What you need to know:

Kibai, who won the men’s the 10,000m and 5000m titles at the Fourth World Deaf Athletics Championships held August 23-28 in Poland, will battle three others athletes for the top honourChelangat will face-off with fellow Tokyo Paralympians, powerlifter Hellen Wawira and rower Asiya Sururu and Beryl Atieno for the women’s top awardSururu became the first female rower to the Paralympic Games where she settled 10th with a time of 14 minutes 27.48 seconds in the single sculls at the 2020 Tokyo Summer Games